{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AJ1yqSdiBA5zE85QQabyAz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 62 tests pass. (The `[FAIL] Story 2-3: failed` in the output is rendered test content from the Ink component, not an actual test failure.)\n\n---\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec.md\n**Status:** Updated to `verifying`\n**Coverage:** 96.99% overall, all 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed\n\n**HIGH: Cost wiped by sprint state polling interval** (`src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`)\n- The 5-second `setInterval` in `run.ts` calls `updateSprintState()` which completely replaced `sprintInfo`, wiping accumulated `totalCost` from `result` events. The `$Y.ZZ spent` display would reset to empty every 5 seconds.\n- **Fix:** `updateSprintState()` now preserves `totalCost`, `acProgress`, and `currentCommand` from the existing state when the incoming update doesn't provide them.\n- **Test added:** \"preserves accumulated cost when updateSprintState is called without cost\"\n\n**MEDIUM: Story key prefix collision in StoryBreakdown** (`src/lib/ink-components.tsx`)\n- `s.key.startsWith(shortKey(sprintInfo.storyKey))` would falsely match story `3-20-foo` when current story is `3-2-bar`, since `\"3-20-foo\".startsWith(\"3-2\")` is true.\n- **Fix:** Changed to exact `shortKey` comparison: `shortKey(s.key) === shortKey(sprintInfo.storyKey)`.\n- **Test added:** \"does not match story 3-20 as current when sprint info says 3-2\"\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Fixed `updateSprintState` to preserve accumulated fields\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Fixed story key matching from `startsWith` to exact comparison\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Added 2 tests for the bugs fixed\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec.md` — Status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling refresh — cost display would flash and disappear\n- MEDIUM: `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches between stories like `3-2` and `3-20`\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `src/commands/run.ts` is 308 lines, 8 lines over the NFR9 300-line limit. Pre-existing issue not introduced by this story.\n- `StoryMessage.type` union lacks an `'info'` variant — the UX spec shows `[INFO] Sprint: 18/65 done (28%)` messages but these can't be rendered through the `StoryMessage` system. Not blocking since INFO messages are informational/transient.\n- `result` event cost is silently dropped if `sprintInfo` is null (edge case — sprintInfo is always set before child process starts, but defensive coding would accumulate cost independently).\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Controller tests for `startRenderer` verify behavior through side effects (no errors thrown) rather than asserting internal state. The cost accumulation test trusts the fix works but can't directly inspect the `state.sprintInfo.totalCost` value from outside.\n- No integration test for the full `run.ts` → `ink-renderer` → component rendering pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The renderer accumulates cost internally but the polling caller has no way to read it back. If cost tracking needs to be reported elsewhere (e.g., in the JSON output on exit), it's currently inaccessible. A shared cost accumulator outside the renderer might be cleaner.\n- `updateSprintState` now has implicit merge behavior (preserving some fields, replacing others) which is a subtle API contract. A more explicit API like `patchSprintState(partial)` vs `setSprintState(full)` would be clearer."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa00a2c3b03dc5f18 (use SendMessage with to: 'aa00a2c3b03dc5f18' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76143\ntool_uses: 48\nduration_ms: 234886</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e8c45fc-a757-4d77-9a55-f32a41bfdb65","uuid":"05e619a7-b439-4f1b-9f46-87f84682199e","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:01:30.191Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"aa00a2c3b03dc5f18","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 62 tests pass. (The `[FAIL] Story 2-3: failed` in the output is rendered test content from the Ink component, not an actual test failure.)\n\n---\n\n## Code Review Summary\n\n**Story:** 6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec.md\n**Status:** Updated to `verifying`\n**Coverage:** 96.99% overall, all 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed\n\n**HIGH: Cost wiped by sprint state polling interval** (`src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`)\n- The 5-second `setInterval` in `run.ts` calls `updateSprintState()` which completely replaced `sprintInfo`, wiping accumulated `totalCost` from `result` events. The `$Y.ZZ spent` display would reset to empty every 5 seconds.\n- **Fix:** `updateSprintState()` now preserves `totalCost`, `acProgress`, and `currentCommand` from the existing state when the incoming update doesn't provide them.\n- **Test added:** \"preserves accumulated cost when updateSprintState is called without cost\"\n\n**MEDIUM: Story key prefix collision in StoryBreakdown** (`src/lib/ink-components.tsx`)\n- `s.key.startsWith(shortKey(sprintInfo.storyKey))` would falsely match story `3-20-foo` when current story is `3-2-bar`, since `\"3-20-foo\".startsWith(\"3-2\")` is true.\n- **Fix:** Changed to exact `shortKey` comparison: `shortKey(s.key) === shortKey(sprintInfo.storyKey)`.\n- **Test added:** \"does not match story 3-20 as current when sprint info says 3-2\"\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Fixed `updateSprintState` to preserve accumulated fields\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Fixed story key matching from `startsWith` to exact comparison\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — Added 2 tests for the bugs fixed\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/6-1-rewrite-ink-components-match-ux-spec.md` — Status updated to `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: `updateSprintState()` wiped accumulated `totalCost` every 5s during polling refresh — cost display would flash and disappear\n- MEDIUM: `startsWith` key comparison in `StoryBreakdown` caused false matches between stories like `3-2` and `3-20`\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- `src/commands/run.ts` is 308 lines, 8 lines over the NFR9 300-line limit. Pre-existing issue not introduced by this story.\n- `StoryMessage.type` union lacks an `'info'` variant — the UX spec shows `[INFO] Sprint: 18/65 done (28%)` messages but these can't be rendered through the `StoryMessage` system. Not blocking since INFO messages are informational/transient.\n- `result` event cost is silently dropped if `sprintInfo` is null (edge case — sprintInfo is always set before child process starts, but defensive coding would accumulate cost independently).\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Controller tests for `startRenderer` verify behavior through side effects (no errors thrown) rather than asserting internal state. The cost accumulation test trusts the fix works but can't directly inspect the `state.sprintInfo.totalCost` value from outside.\n- No integration test for the full `run.ts` → `ink-renderer` → component rendering pipeline with cost accumulation across polling cycles.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The renderer accumulates cost internally but the polling caller has no way to read it back. If cost tracking needs to be reported elsewhere (e.g., in the JSON output on exit), it's currently inaccessible. A shared cost accumulator outside the renderer might be cleaner.\n- `updateSprintState` now has implicit merge behavior (preserving some fields, replacing others) which is a subtle API contract. A more explicit API like `patchSprintState(partial)` vs `setSprintState(full)` would be clearer."}],"totalDurationMs":234886,"totalTokens":76143,"totalToolUseCount":48,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1411,"cache_read_input_tokens":73658,"output_tokens":1073,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1411},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
