{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ewut4sTJDoELkLQ3GgDFBv","type":"tool_result","content":"  1390→| Coverage-tracked files | 119 | 121 | +2 |\n  1391→| Overall coverage | 96.97% | 96.98% | steady |\n  1392→| Releases shipped | 0 | 2 (v0.23.0, v0.23.1) | +2 |\n  1393→| Bugs found & fixed | 0 | 17 | +17 |\n  1394→| Tech debt items opened | 0 | 12 | +12 |\n  1395→| Tech debt items resolved | 0 | 0 | 0 |\n  1396→| Retro entries this day | 0 | 8 | (too many) |\n  1397→\n  1398→---\n  1399→\n  1400→## Sprint Health Assessment\n  1401→\n  1402→The Operational Excellence Sprint is effectively complete. All committed scope (Epics 1-5) is done. Epics 0 and 0.5 (stretch/bonus epics added mid-sprint) are also done. The remaining 6 stories in Epics 6 and 7 are backlog items — they were planned as onboarding compliance gaps and are not blocking any release or user-facing feature.\n  1403→\n  1404→**The sprint's biggest success:** The 4-phase pipeline and session issues log proved their value. 17 bugs found and fixed, 75% caught by code review, with verify catching the integration seam bugs that review missed.\n  1405→\n  1406→**The sprint's biggest failure:** Tech debt resolution rate is 0%. Twelve items accumulated, none resolved. The retro process identified the right issues but the execution loop never dedicated time to fix them. The skipped BATS tests are the poster child: flagged as urgent in every retro, ignored in every session.\n  1407→\n  1408→**Recommendation for next sprint:**\n  1409→1. Dedicate the first session to tech debt: fix verify-env patches, readPatchFile path resolution, tree-shaking issue, and BATS tests. These 4 items are genuine blockers or quality gaps.\n  1410→2. Reduce retro frequency to 2 per day max (mid-day checkpoint + end-of-day consolidation). Eight retros created more overhead than value.\n  1411→3. Before starting Epic 6 or 7, ensure the verification infrastructure actually works for patch-modifying and export-dependent stories. Otherwise those stories will hit the same blockers.\n  1412→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01M69Sq1o5Nvxqyf7xgGumDp","session_id":"3e8c45fc-a757-4d77-9a55-f32a41bfdb65","uuid":"82765764-3e8d-4359-b75d-fbb14baef556","timestamp":"2026-03-21T11:02:28.316Z"}
